          <p>"A thing is right when it tends to preserve the integrity, stability, and beauty of the biotic community. It is wrong when it tends otherwise." — Aldo Leopold</p>
        </div>
        <p>Leopold expanded the moral community beyond humans to include soils, waters, plants, and animals — the entire "land community."</p>

        <h4 class="green-h">Deep Ecology (Arne Naess)</h4>
